{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "/hsy-audit-last-run",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "\n\n## Autonomous Execution Context\n\nYou are being executed by the HSY Autonomous Orchestrator. Please:\n\n1. **Be decisive**: Make reasonable assumptions when information is incomplete\n2. **Provide structured output**: Use clear formatting for the orchestrator to parse\n3. **Include confidence ratings**: Rate your confidence in decisions (High/Medium/Low)\n4. **Note uncertainties**: Clearly indicate any areas needing human review\n5. **Suggest next steps**: Always suggest the most logical next hook\n\n**Autonomy Level**: Full (with human fallback)\n**Execution Mode**: Production\n**Safety Checks**: Enabled\n\nA coding / working round was currently achieved. If everything went right, this should be relative to completing partly or fully one phase of the currently ongoing implementation plan. Check the ./docs/planning directory. You should see one or more files containing detailed implementation plans, named as such : \"IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_<number>_<tag>\". One of them should be carrying the tag \"ongoing\" (example : \"IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_12_ongoing\"). Analyse it carefully : you will notice phases and/or items displaying on their respective header a ticked \"Ran\" box, but an unticked \"Audited\" box. Focus only on these ones : as you correctly assumed, it means these steps were just executed but have not been reviewed. \nOn all items (within phases) and phases (groups of items) involved, you will notice useful information : under [CREATED_x.x_FILES] and [EDITED_x.x_FILES] are listed codebase files of which diff must be analyzed. (Note that _x.x_ are or, if not, must be replaced to represent, for items, _<phase>_<item_number>_, and logically, <phase> if current part is about the entire phase).\n\nUnder [COMPLETION_x.x_NOTES] should be found some information left by the agent in charge of this work ; it is organised in categories, of which some can optionally be left empty : <CONFIDENCE> (how sure the agent is that the item (for item feedback) or phase (for phase feedback) is fully and perfectly (prod-ready) implemented in the best possible way). <DOUBTS> (elements the agent stumbled upon or simply would like extra care to be given upon reviewing to ensure full prod-ready code). <LEARNINGS> (useful insights that occured to the agent during this work run : potential pitfalls, useful advice, memory addings, best practices, important focuses...). <OTHER> (any additional comment from the agent before, during, or after their work). Read all of it carefully.\n\nProceed with reading manually, systematically and with utmost care ALL referenced file within this work run. Confront it to : \n1) for items, [ITEM_x.x_DESCRIPTION] and [ITEM_x.x_GOALS] ; for phases, to [PHASE_x_GOAL], [PHASE_x_SUCCESS_CRITERIA], [PHASE_x_IMPORTANT_NOTES]. \n2) To all the information referenced into ./docs/goals_and_principles directory : BEST_PRACTICES.md ; IMPORTANT_LEARNINGS.md ; DO_NOT_DO.md ; PITFALLS_AND_ADVICE.md ; GOALS_AND_PHILOSOPHY.md ; END_USER_WISH_INTROSPECTION.md . \n3) Then, compare all submitted work to references from ./docs/technical directory : TECH_STACK.md ; LANGUAGE_AND_BRANDING.md ; APIs.md ; EXTERNAL_SERVICES.md ; VARIABLES.md ; FRONTEND.md ; BACKEND.md ; ARCHITECTURE.md ; DATA_TABLES.md ; ENV_EXAMPLES.md - once fully confronted, one by one, all worked on files, all documentation files : \n4) Confront, now, with absolute care for quality, security, and unbeatable end user experience with no issue, to your knowledge. Analyze every code line, every function, every tool, every component, every feature, every tweak. Check all files and all lines with your learnings on the project in mind. Do not use grep. Read EVERY file manually. Spot any mock implementation, any incomplete feature, any, even slightest divergence between an element marked as « completed » and the reality of the codebase. Only the actual code is the source of truth.\nDo not let anything pass. Ensure best-in-class UI, UX, SECURITY, FEATURE FUNCTION, CODE QUALITY, ROUTING, ERROR AND EMPTY STATE HANDLING, DESIGN, BRANDING, API CALLS, FALLBACKS, LOGIC, AND ANY ASPECT THAT COULD AT ANY POINT IMPACT THE USER. —> REMEMBER THE KEY PRINCIPLE : YOU ARE THE EXPERT HERE, AND YOU LET CODE PASS OR NOT. ANYTHING YOU MARK AS PASS IS UPON YOUR RESPONSIBILITY. YOU HAVE BEEN CHOSEN BECAUSE YOU ARE THE BEST AT CODE REVIEW, BECAUSE NOTHING EVER ESCAPES YOUR TRAINED EYE. TICKED AS COMPLETED ALWAYS, WITH NO EXCEPTION, MEANS FULLY READY FOR PRODUCTION. THE TINIEST CODE SNIPPET YOU VALIDATE COULD BE SENT AS ITSELF AND NEVER REFACTORED. YOU ARE THE ULTIMATE GUARDIAN. ANY DOUBT YOU HAVE MUST BE FLAGGED. ANY UNSTABLE EXECUTION OR IMPLEMENTATION. — Get back to the current « IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_x_ongoing ».\n\nOn the item(s) and/or phase(s) you are reviewing, below the previously filled fields that the working agent completed for you, you will see two paragraphs with a title and for each, under the title, a placeholder for your contribution : [AUDIT_x.x_RESULTS] and [FIXING_x.x_PLAN]. For audit results, you will replace the placeholder with extremely detailed itemized outputs on your findings to refactor or improve, conducted with ultimate severity. Use category tags to help the refactoring agent. \nThe fixing plan will provide steps and guidance to fix perfectly the issues raised and improve until fully prod-ready. Format your contribution as such - GOOD FORMATTING FOR FINAL OUTPUT REPLACING PLACEHOLDERS INTO IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_<number>_<tag>.md FOR EACH ITEM AND PHASE AUDITED  :\n\n<…>\n\n[AUDIT_x.x_RESULTS]\n1. <tags : examples : <UX> ; <SECURITY> ; <GOAL_COMPLIANCE> …>\n<files involved : <absolute_path>.<filetype> ; <absolute_path>.<filetype> ; … >\nVerbose, dev and agentic coding agent oriented detailed overview of the issue or doubt, and what     risks it raises for safety, user satisfaction, function, stability, etc…\n2. …\n\n[FIXING_x.x_PLAN]\n1. <title of the step>\n<files involved>\n<comprehensive guidance and snippets for proper and ensured fixing and improving>\n<pitfalls to avoid>\n<important checks>\n<fix success criteria>\n2. …\n\n——-\n\nCONGRATULATIONS : once every single item and phase that was ticked as « Ran » but not yet as « Audited » has been thoroughly analyzed in regards to all provided instructions and audited+documented with all requirements, the core task is done.\nVERY IMPORTANT ; NOW :\n- Mark all items and/or phases you audited as « Audited » in the tick box.\n- Read through all completed work and audit, especially at notes and learnings. Assess which provided information has relevant interested in being referenced « above » for longer term implementation ; when deemed important to remain constantly considered, rewrite, refine and enrich parts of the documentation freshly provided by the working agent and by you to populate the files into ./docs/goals_and_principles directory : BEST_PRACTICES.md ; IMPORTANT_LEARNINGS.md ; DO_NOT_DO.md ; PITFALLS_AND_ADVICE.md ; GOALS_AND_PHILOSOPHY.md ; END_USER_WISH_INTROSPECTION.md\n- Review all the code written ; based on fresh implementations, check for updates and edits to potentially perform with utmost care into references from ./docs/technical directory : TECH_STACK.md ; LANGUAGE_AND_BRANDING.md ; APIs.md ; EXTERNAL_SERVICES.md ; VARIABLES.md ; FRONTEND.md ; BACKEND.md ; ARCHITECTURE.md ; DATA_TABLES.md ; ENV_EXAMPLES.md\n- Re read the entire instructions and ensure not a single element of the request or of the fresh work has been omitted.\n- Once fully confident : you did it. Time to pass on. Three possibilities :\n- IF items remain in the currently executed phase : run command : /hsy-postaudit-apply-fixes-continue-phase\n- IF the work you audited covered all items of the current phase : run command /hsy-postaudit-apply-fixes-new-phase\n- IF the work you audited was addressing ALL remaining items of the LAST phase of the current IMPLEMENTATION PLAN : run command /hsy-postaudit-apply-fixes-plan-prevalidate."
  },
  "workspaceFolderName": "cleanstart",
  "shortName": "hsy-audit-last-run",
  "metadata": {
    "autonomy": {
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "confidenceThreshold": 0.7,
      "requiresHumanInput": false,
      "estimatedDuration": "5m",
      "resourceRequirements": {
        "memory": "medium",
        "cpu": "medium",
        "model": "default"
      },
      "safetyChecks": [
        "file-backup",
        "dry-run-available",
        "rollback-supported"
      ]
    }
  }
}